# No AI-style comments

- Do not add explanatory, redundant, or "here we do X" comments in any code we develop.
- Do not add comments that describe what the code obviously does (e.g. "// Loop through items", "// Return the result").
- Only add comments when they explain non-obvious why, constraints, or gotchas; keep them short and factual.
